    "location": "Taub Building",
    "abstract": "We introduce the sum channel, a new channel model motivated by applications in distributed storage and DNA data storage. In the error-free case, it takes as input an $\\ell$-row binary matrix and outputs an $(\\ell+1)$-row matrix whose first $\\ell$ rows equal the input and whose last row is their parity (sum) row.\r\nWe construct a two-deletion-correcting code with redundancy $2\\lceil\\log_2\\log_2 n\\rceil+ \\log_2 \\ell + O(1)$ for $\\ell$-row inputs. When $\\ell=2$, we establish...\n                          [ Full version ]",
